The paper discusses the use of pretraining techniques for deep learning, which is a common topic in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of unsupervised learning procedures, which is a common topic in the subfield of neural networks (cs.NE). The experiments conducted in the paper involve image classification (MNIST) and audio analysis (Birdsong), which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), respectively. Finally, the paper discusses the role of regularization and optimization in pretraining, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
